{"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"final","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Swimmer"}],"platforms":["Linux"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"Description","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Description"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This environment corresponds to the Swimmer environment described in Rémi Coulom’s PhD thesis"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/tel.archives-ouvertes.fr\/tel-00003985\/document","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The environment aims to increase the number of independent state and control","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"variables as compared to the classic control environments. The swimmers","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"consist of three or more segments (’","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"links"}],"type":"strong"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":"’) and one less articulation","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"joints (’","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"rotors","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":"’) - one rotor joint connecting exactly two links to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"form a linear chain. The swimmer is suspended in a two dimensional pool and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"always starts in the same position (subject to some deviation drawn from an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"uniform distribution), and the goal is to move as fast as possible towards","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the right by applying torque on the rotors and using the fluids friction.","type":"text"}]},{"text":"Notes","level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"Notes"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The problem parameters are:","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Problem parameters:","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"n"}]},{"type":"text","text":": number of body parts"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"m"},{"type":"text","text":"i"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":": mass of part "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"i"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" ("},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"i"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" ∈ {1…n})"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"l"},{"type":"text","text":"i"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":": length of part "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"i"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" ("},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"i","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" ∈ {1…n})"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"k","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":": viscous-friction coefficient","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"While the default environment has ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"n","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" = 3, ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"l"},{"type":"text","text":"i"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" = 0.1,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"k"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" = 0.1. It is possible to pass a custom MuJoCo XML file during construction to increase the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"number of links, or to tweak any of the parameters.","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"text":"Action Space","level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"Action-Space"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The action space is a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Box(-1, 1, (2,), float32)"},{"type":"text","text":". An action represents the torques applied between "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"links","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"}]},{"header":"row","rows":[[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Num","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Action"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Control Min"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Control Max"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Name (in corresponding XML file)","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Joint"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Unit"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"0"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Torque applied on the first rotor","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"-1","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"1","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"motor1_rot","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"hinge"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"torque (N m)","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"1"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Torque applied on the second rotor","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"-1","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"1"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"motor2_rot"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"hinge","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"torque (N m)"}]}]]],"type":"table"},{"text":"Observation Space","level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"Observation-Space"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"By default, observations consists of:","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"θ","type":"text"},{"text":"i","type":"text"},{"text":": angle of part ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"i"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" with respect to the ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"x"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" axis","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"θ"},{"type":"text","text":"i"},{"type":"text","text":"’: its derivative with respect to time (angular velocity)"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"In the default case, observations do not include the x- and y-coordinates of the front tip. These may"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"be included by passing "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"exclude_current_positions_from_observation=False"},{"type":"text","text":" during construction."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Then, the observation space will have 10 dimensions where the first two dimensions"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"represent the x- and y-coordinates of the front tip."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Regardless of whether "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"exclude_current_positions_from_observation"},{"type":"text","text":" was set to true or false, the x- and y-coordinates"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"will be returned in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"info"},{"type":"text","text":" with keys "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"x_position\""},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"y_position\""},{"type":"text","text":", respectively."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"By default, the observation is a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ndarray"},{"type":"text","text":" with shape "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"(8,)"},{"type":"text","text":" where the elements correspond to the following:"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"| Num | Observation                          | Min  | Max | Name (in corresponding XML file) | Joint | Unit                     |"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"| — | ———————————— | –– | — | –––––––––––––––– | —– | ———————— |"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"| 0   | angle of the front tip               | -Inf | Inf | free_body_rot                    | hinge | angle (rad)              |"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"| 1   | angle of the first rotor             | -Inf | Inf | motor1_rot                       | hinge | angle (rad)              |"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"| 2   | angle of the second rotor            | -Inf | Inf | motor2_rot                       | hinge | angle (rad)              |"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"| 3   | velocity of the tip along the x-axis | -Inf | Inf | slider1                          | slide | velocity (m\/s)           |"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"| 4   | velocity of the tip along the y-axis | -Inf | Inf | slider2                          | slide | velocity (m\/s)           |"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"| 5   | angular velocity of front tip        | -Inf | Inf | free_body_rot                    | hinge | angular velocity (rad\/s) |"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"| 6   | angular velocity of first rotor      | -Inf | Inf | motor1_rot                       | hinge | angular velocity (rad\/s) |"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"| 7   | angular velocity of second rotor     | -Inf | Inf | motor2_rot                             | hinge | angular velocity (rad\/s) |"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"text":"Rewards","level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"Rewards"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The reward consists of two parts:","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"forward_reward"}]},{"type":"text","text":": A reward of moving forward which is measured"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"as "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"forward_reward_weight"},{"type":"text","text":" * (x-coordinate before action - x-coordinate after action)\/dt"}]},{"type":"text","text":". "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"dt","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the time between actions and is dependent on the frame_skip parameter"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(default is 4), where the frametime is 0.01 - making the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"default "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"dt = 4 * 0.01 = 0.04","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":". This reward would be positive if the swimmer"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"swims right as desired."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"ctrl_cost","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":": A cost for penalising the swimmer if it takes"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"actions that are too large. It is measured as "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ctrl_cost_weight"},{"text":" *","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"sum(action","type":"text"},{"text":"2","type":"text"},{"text":")","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" where "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ctrl_cost_weight"}]},{"type":"text","text":" is a parameter set for the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"control and has a default value of 1e-4"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The total reward returned is "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"reward","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"}]},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"=","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"forward_reward - ctrl_cost"}]},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"info"},{"type":"text","text":" will also contain the individual reward terms"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"text":"Starting State","level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"Starting-State"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"All observations start in state (0,0,0,0,0,0,0,0) with a Uniform noise in the range of [-","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"reset_noise_scale"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"reset_noise_scale"},{"text":"] is added to the initial state for stochasticity.","type":"text"}]},{"text":"Episode End","level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"Episode-End"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The episode truncates when the episode length is greater than 1000."}]},{"text":"Arguments","level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"Arguments"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"No additional arguments are currently supported in v2 and lower.","type":"text"}]},{"code":["gym.make('Swimmer-v4')"],"syntax":null,"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"v3 and v4 take gym.make kwargs such as xml_file, ctrl_cost_weight, reset_noise_scale etc.","type":"text"}]},{"code":["env = gym.make('Swimmer-v4', ctrl_cost_weight=0.1, ....)"],"syntax":null,"type":"codeListing"},{"header":"row","rows":[[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Parameter"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Type"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Default","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Description","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"xml_file"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"str"}],"type":"strong"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"\"swimmer.xml\"","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Path to a MuJoCo model","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"forward_reward_weight","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"float"}],"type":"strong"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"1.0","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Weight for ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"forward_reward","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" term (see section on reward)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"ctrl_cost_weight","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"float"}],"type":"strong"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"1e-4"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Weight for "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"ctrl_cost"}]},{"type":"text","text":" term (see section on reward)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"reset_noise_scale"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"float","type":"text"}]}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"0.1","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Scale of random perturbations of initial position and velocity (see section on Starting State)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"exclude_current_positions_from_observation"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"bool","type":"text"}]}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"True"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Whether or not to omit the x- and y-coordinates from observations. Excluding the position can serve as an inductive bias to induce position-agnostic behavior in policies","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]]],"type":"table"},{"text":"Version History","level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"Version-History"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"v4: all mujoco environments now use the mujoco bindings in mujoco>=2.1.3","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"v3: support for gym.make kwargs such as xml_file, ctrl_cost_weight, reset_noise_scale etc. rgb rendering comes from tracking camera (so agent does not run away from screen)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"v2: All continuous control environments now use mujoco_py >= 1.50","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"v1: max_time_steps raised to 1000 for robot based tasks. Added reward_threshold to environments."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"v0: Initial versions release (1.0.0)"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}]}],"topicSections":[{"title":"Initializers","identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/Gym\/Swimmer\/init(forwardRewardWeight:ctrlCostWeight:resetNoiseScale:)"]},{"title":"Instance Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/Gym\/Swimmer\/data","doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/Gym\/Swimmer\/model"]},{"title":"Default Implementations","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/Gym\/Swimmer\/Env-Implementations"]}],"kind":"symbol","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/Gym"]]},"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Class","title":"Swimmer","externalID":"s:3Gym7SwimmerC","symbolKind":"class","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Swimmer"}],"role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Swimmer"}],"modules":[{"name":"Gym"}]},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/Gym\/Swimmer"},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"relationshipsSections":[{"title":"Conforms To","kind":"relationships","identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/Gym\/Env","doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/Gym\/MuJoCoEnv"],"type":"conformsTo"}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/gym\/swimmer"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"references":{"doc://org.liuliu.s4nnc/documentation/Gym/Swimmer/Env-Implementations":{"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/Gym\/Swimmer\/Env-Implementations","url":"\/documentation\/gym\/swimmer\/env-implementations","role":"collectionGroup","title":"Env Implementations","abstract":[],"kind":"article"},"https://tel.archives-ouvertes.fr/tel-00003985/document":{"type":"link","title":"“Reinforcement Learning Using Neural Networks, with Applications to Motor Control”","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"“Reinforcement Learning Using Neural Networks, with Applications to Motor Control”"}],"url":"https:\/\/tel.archives-ouvertes.fr\/tel-00003985\/document","identifier":"https:\/\/tel.archives-ouvertes.fr\/tel-00003985\/document"},"doc://org.liuliu.s4nnc/documentation/Gym/MuJoCoEnv":{"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/Gym\/MuJoCoEnv","url":"\/documentation\/gym\/mujocoenv","abstract":[],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"MuJoCoEnv","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MuJoCoEnv"}],"title":"MuJoCoEnv"},"doc://org.liuliu.s4nnc/documentation/Gym":{"type":"topic","abstract":[],"title":"Gym","kind":"symbol","ur